main event: A resident of Point Pleasant, New Jersey reported observing a bright satellite moving in a southeast direction on August 9, 1961.
interesting points: The satellite appeared to be on a different orbit than other smaller satellites observed at the same time.
The resident had observed the same satellite on other occasions and found its movements to be quite uncommon.
The resident requested information from the Air Force about the identity and nature of the satellite they had observed.
The Air Force responded by requesting more detailed information about the sighting, such as the time, elevation, direction, duration, size, and blinking/twinkling of the object.
The Air Force indicated they were unable to identify the object based on the initial information provided and sought additional details to attempt an identification.
sighted object: a bright satellite moving in a southeast direction
